org.araneaframework.uilib.util
Interface DisplayItemContainer<T>

All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseSelectControl, DefaultMultiSelectControl, DefaultSelectControl, MultiSelectControl, SelectControl
public interface DisplayItemContainer<T>

The base specification for containers that deal with display items.

Author:
Jevgeni Kabanov (ekabanov@araneaframework.org)

getGroups

List<SelectGroup<T>> getGroups()
Returns a list of all groups that this DisplayItemContainer currently holds. The returned groups must also provide all the values that belong to that group.

Returns:
A list of all contained display item groups.
Since:
2.0

getAllItems

List<T> getAllItems()
Returns a list of display items that this DisplayItemContainer currently holds.

Returns:
A list of all contained display items.
Since:
2.0

getEnabledItems

List<T> getEnabledItems()
Returns a list of display items that this DisplayItemContainer currently holds and that are enabled for selection. When this container does not distinguish enabled/disabled display items, this method will always return the same result as getAllItems().

Returns:
A list of enabled display items.
Since:
2.0

getDisabledItems

List<T> getDisabledItems()
Returns a list of display items that this DisplayItemContainer currently holds and that are disabled from being selected. When this container does not distinguish enabled/disabled display items, this method will always return an empty list.

Returns:
A list of disabled display items.
Since:
2.0

getItemLabelProperty

String getItemLabelProperty()
When the underlying DisplayItemContainer uses a bean property to resolve its label, the method returns the property name. Otherwise, returns null.

Returns:
The property of a display item to resolve its label, or null.
